# Docs Context First
- Before coding or refactoring, quickly read project context docs in `docs/`.
- Start with `docs/project-overview-for-ai.md` for current architecture and module ownership.
- Then review `docs/chrome-extension-markdown-viewer-plan.md` for roadmap/phase intent.
- For performance-related tasks, also read `docs/performance-issues-audit.md`.
- If the task maps to a specific phase, read the matching file in `docs/technical-spec-phases/`.
- For reader theme presets, Shiki highlighting, or fenced-code CSS, follow `.cursor/rules/35-reader-theme-and-shiki.mdc`.
- Treat docs as guidance and source code in `src/` as final runtime truth when conflicts appear.
